Mechanical design and structural development of the Adaptive Quadruped Robot (AQR), including TinkerCAD model, assembly design, torque calculations, and component integration

1. Robot Specifications
Robot Name: AQR (Adaptive Quadruped Robot)
Number of Legs: 4
Degrees of Freedom (DOF): 8 (2 DOF per leg)
Actuators: MG996R Servo Motors

2. Mechanical Dimensions :

 Body Length 120 mm
 Body Width 80 mm
 Body Height 25 mm
 Upper Leg Length 50 mm
 Lower Leg Length 60 mm

3. Estimated Robot Weight

 Chassis 0.60 kg
 Battery 0.35 kg
 Arduino + Electronics 0.10 kg
 Eight Servo Motors 0.60 kg
 Four Legs 0.35 kg
 Total Weight 2.00 kg
m = 2.0 kg

4. Gravitational Force

The gravitational acceleration is:

g = 9.81\;m/s^2

The total weight force acting on the robot is:

F = mg

F = 2.0 \times 9.81

F = 19.62\;N

5. Load Distribution Per Leg

Assuming the robot is standing on four legs and the weight is evenly distributed:

F_{leg}=\frac{19.62}{4}

F_{leg}=4.905\;N

Each leg supports approximately 4.9 N under static conditions.


6. Hip Joint Torque Calculation

The upper leg length is:

L = 50\;mm = 0.05\;m

The required torque is calculated by:

T = F \times L

T = 4.905 \times 0.05

T = 0.245\;N\cdot m

Therefore, the minimum required torque at the hip joint is:

\boxed{T = 0.245\;N\cdot m}

7. Safety Factor

A safety factor of 2 is selected for mechanical reliability.

T_{design}=2\times0.245

T_{design}=0.49\;N\cdot m

Therefore, each actuator should provide at least

T>0.5\;N\cdot m

8. Servo Motor Selection

Selected Motor: MG996R Servo

Typical output torque:

1.0\sim1.1\;N\cdot m

Since

1.0 > 0.49

the selected servo provides an adequate safety margin and is suitable for the proposed design.

9. Center of Gravity (CG)

To improve stability, the robot components are arranged as follows:

The battery is positioned at the center of the chassis.
The Arduino controller is mounted directly above the battery.
The four legs are symmetrically distributed around the body.

10. Walking Gait

The selected locomotion method is the Crawl Gait, which offers high stability during motion.
11. Material Selection

Selected Material: PLA Plastic

PLA was chosen because it:

Is lightweight.
Has a low manufacturing cost.
Is easy to fabricate using 3D printing.
Is well suited for prototype development.
Provides sufficient strength for a small educational quadruped robot.
